episodes.overview: Sara Haines tries to keep the winning streak alive when she teams up with Food Network's Anne Burrell to try to bring Bobby Flay down. Chefs Jonathan Dearden and Scott Drewno go head-to-head for a shot at Bobby's crown.

episodes.name: Friday Night Bites
episodes.overview: Ultracompetitive Food Network pals Amanda Freitag and Sunny Anderson team up to tackle, trounce and otherwise demolish Bobby Flay on an even playing field. Tampa chef Michael Buttacavoli and New Jersey's Chef Scott McDonald face off on the gridiron to put a big fat L in Bobby's record.

episodes.name: Who's the Boss
episodes.overview: Actor and Food Network superfan Ben Rappaport teams up with Chopped judge Amanda Freitag for an extra special behind-the-scenes episode. Things get personal when two people who know Bobby Flay better than anyone -- culinary producer Katie Renda and culinary stylist Richmond Flores -- try to beat their boss!

episodes.name: It's All Gravy
episodes.overview: Saturday Night Live's Ego Nwodim tag-teams with Bobby Flay's pal, Chef Michael Symon, to improvise their way to a win in Bobby's kitchen. Rock-star chefs Brandon Baltzley and Bill Crites must think on the fly if they want to walk out with a win.

episodes.name: Too Fly for Flay
episodes.overview: Actress Nicole Ari Parker tries to build a winning empire as she teams up with The Kitchen's Sunny Anderson to take down Bobby Flay. Husband-and-wife chefs Julio Lazzarini and Jennifer Behm-Lazzarini have to battle one another before getting a chance to steal the sash and tiara from Bobby.

episodes.name: Belly Up!
episodes.overview: Meat masters Max Hosey and Ash Fulk go belly up for the star ingredient as they battle for a shot at Bobby Flay. Then things hit the next level when Bobby and Chef Claire Robinson discover Chef Scott Conant's secret obsession with the winning contender's signature dish.

episodes.name: If I Dip, You Dip, We Dip
episodes.overview: Legendary actress and funnywoman Ana Gasteyer has Bobby Flay in stitches as she and Bobby's pal Chef Josh Capon try to take him down. Bobby has to dip and dodge Ana's comedic barbs as he takes on chefs Sarah Cloyd and Danny Brown, who are looking to humor themselves with a win.

episodes.name: You Made Your Bread, Now Eat It
episodes.overview: Acclaimed chef Michael Voltaggio and TV host Jaymee Sire pair up to topple Bobby Flay. They bring in Yehuda Sichel and Remy Pettus, two young and hungry chefs hot on the path to take down the culinary king.

episodes.name: Power Trip
episodes.overview: Actor Joseph Sikora of the series Power joins Michael Symon to bring the muscle into Bobby Flay's kitchen. They recruit superchefs Ian Rynecki and Ruth Wigman to put the squeeze on Bobby as they try to best him with a win.

episodes.name: A Berry Crazy Night
episodes.overview: Food Network's Eddie Jackson and Anne Burrell hope to trip up Bobby Flay with some stellar competition. Things come down to the wire between chefs Nokee Bucayu and Jay Reifel, leaving Anne, Eddie and Bobby all on the edge of their seats!

episodes.name: Best in Snow
episodes.overview: Food Network's Sunny Anderson and Christian Petroni set hearts and hearths ablaze as they try to snow in Bobby Flay for the season. Minnesota-native chefs Karyn Tomlinson and Erick Harcey do their best to bring the frigid winter to Bobby's kitchen.

episodes.name: Veggin' Out
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay brings out special guest, activist Beth Stern, along with Food Network's Katie Lee, for an all-vegetarian battle. Vegetarian chefs Cara Nance and Destiny Aponte are down for the challenge because they're all about that veg -- no trouble!

episodes.name: Flirting with Victory
episodes.overview: Chef Alex Guarnaschelli gets an assist from actress Malin Akerman, who proves to be more of a distraction than Bobby Flay can handle. Chefs Andrew Bent and Alejandro Barrientos try to steal a win while Malin runs interference in Bobby's kitchen.

episodes.name: The Battle for Saratoga
episodes.overview: Golf phenom Michelle Wie joins Food Network's Scott Conant to add a stroke to Bobby Flay's game. Saratoga, N.Y., chefs Jeannette Liebers and Chris Bonnivier are on the scene to make sure Bobby takes a mulligan as they duke it out for the title of best brunch in town.

episodes.name: Peas of Mind
episodes.overview: Actress Lela Loren, star of Power, pairs up with Bobby Flay's pal Michael Symon to try to get Bobby to power down in his own kitchen. International chefs Lien Lin and Hamidullah Noori attempt to throw Bobby a curve ball with a dish he's never heard of.

episodes.name: Mission: Impastable
episodes.overview: Food Network's Chef Anne Burrell brings rising star comedian Jaboukie Young White from The Daily Show to hit Bobby Flay with some breaking news: He's going down. They recruit Italian expert chefs Nicole Karr and David Benstock to make Bobby say "Ciao!"

episodes.name: Rambutan Rumble
episodes.overview: Global chefs Dannie Harrison and Hiro Tawara try to trip up Bobby Flay with some dishes that are off the map! Food Network's Giada De Laurentiis and Marcus Samuelsson are along for the ride and hoping Bobby gets jet lag.

episodes.name: Grin and Camembert It
episodes.overview: Food Network darlings Valerie Bertinelli and Amanda Freitag join forces to turn the tables on Bobby Flay. They bring in New York City chefs Edward Brumfield and Ricardo Barreras, who are in it to win it.

episodes.name: Let the Trumpet Sound!
episodes.overview: VEEP star Reid Scott makes a campaign run against Bobby Flay with an all-star running mate, Food Network's Sunny Anderson. Chefs Ned Baldwin and Sieger Bayer want to veto Bobby's winning record and snag a landslide victory of their own.

episodes.name: Beets Me
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay's friends Damaris Phillips and Michael Symon get together for the very first time to try to take their pal down. He'll have to tango with fellow New Yorkers Andrew Lukovsky and Airis Johnson, who aren't going down without a fight.

episodes.name: The Puck Stops Here
episodes.overview: Culinary legend Wolfgang Puck makes his first-ever appearance at the Beat Bobby Flay arena alongside Chopped guru Ted Allen. Chefs Emily Hansen and Judy Anderson must impress the dynamic duo to get the chance to fillet the Flay.

episodes.name: Kelly and the Jet
episodes.overview: Former Olympian and chef Dawn Burrell and West Coast legend, Chef Rob Lam, must face off before they go for the gold against Bobby Flay. Food Network's Clinton Kelly and Jet Tila are there to cheer them on to victory.

episodes.name: Best Dressed in TV
episodes.overview: The most-fashionable men on TV, Chef Geoffrey Zakarian and TV host Carson Kressley, team up to take down Bobby Flay and tackle his basic button-down fashion choices. Seasoned chefs Chris Coleman and Siddharth Krishna hope to claim a head-turning win.

episodes.name: Bobby and the Chocolate Factory
episodes.overview: Chopped judge Alex Guarnaschelli teams up with Chopped Sweets judge Elizabeth Chambers to give Bobby Flay some bittersweet memories. They recruit chefs Leanne Mascoli and Melanie Moss, who are sweet on walking away with a win.

episodes.name: Hate to Burst Your Shark
episodes.overview: Things heat up in this summertime battle as chefs Phelix Gardner and Enrika Williams try to make a splash with a win in Bobby Flay's kitchen. Bobby uses his chef knives to try and slash the summer fun for Food Network's Eddie Jackson and Ted Allen.

episodes.name: It's All Jackfruit to Me
episodes.overview: Chefs Jonathan Meyer and Fernanda Tapia are thrown for a loop when Bobby Flay gives them a challenging star ingredient. Chef Alex Guarnaschelli and Man v. Food's Casey Webb try to ease the pressure with some pranks to throw Bobby off his game.

episodes.name: Romancing the Flay
episodes.overview: Love is in the air as married couple and chefs Laura and Sayat Ozyilmaz team up to take Bobby Flay down. Chef Michael Voltaggio and Food Network's Jeff Mauro spark a budding bromance, leaving Bobby all by his lonesome.

episodes.name: Last Man Grilling
episodes.overview: Two chefs from out west head to the big city for a grill-off against the grill master himself. Chefs Mark Henry and Larry Delgado hope to leave a grill mark on Bobby Flay's record, while Chef Josh Capon and TV host Laura Vitale try to help smoke Bobby out of his own kitchen.

episodes.name: Scallop Over the Finish Line
episodes.overview: Legendary actor John O'Hurley pairs up with Food Network's Damaris Phillips in trying to catalog all of Bobby Flay's fails. Talented chefs Charlie Fuerte and Jonathan Brooks look to turn the tables on Bobby and leave victorious!

episodes.name: Don't Be Crabby
episodes.overview: Things get heated when Florida chefs Noel Cruz and Andrew Zarzosa face off for a shot at Bobby Flay. Food Network regulars Katie Lee and Eddie Jackson do their best to razz Bobby with a dish he knows nothing about.

episodes.name: A Family Affair
episodes.overview: Chefs Liam Beardslee and Nicole Gomes get an unlikely supporter as Bobby Flay's daughter, Sophie Flay, joins Chef Alex Guarnaschelli to show that she's the Flay in first. Can Bobby put family matters aside, or will Sophie take home the family crown this time?

episodes.name: Adios, Roberto Flay
episodes.overview: Food Network's Anne Burrell and Damaris Phillips team up to hassle, heckle and hope Bobby Flay loses. They bring in Italian master chefs Ayaka Guido and Fabrizio Facchini to say "Adios, Roberto Flay" once and for all.

episodes.name: It's a Cakewalk
episodes.overview: Food Network's Damaris Phillips teams up with the one and only Ace of Cakes, Duff Goldman, in his inaugural appearance to steal a sweet victory from Bobby Flay. Top-notch pastry chefs Holden Jagger and Tova du Plessis must face off for a chance to bake Bobby under the table.

episodes.name: All Tapped Out
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay is in for a treat when he must tackle something sweet against heavy-hitting pastry chefs Lasheeda Perry and Will Gustwiller. The Cake Boss, Buddy Valastro, brings in sportscaster Kathryn Tappen for the pastry battle play-by-play.

episodes.name: It's All Greek to Me
episodes.overview: It's all Greek to Bobby Flay as chefs George Kantaris and Angelo Vangelopoulos take center stage for a shot at the crown. Will it be a comedy or a tragedy for Chef Michael Symon and actress Carly Hughes as they cheer them on?

episodes.name: High Prune
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay's got his back against the wall when two global chefs try to make his world spin! West African chef Godwin Ihentuge and Indian chef Kingshuk Dey battle to bring Bobby down, with a little heckling help from Food Network's Sunny Anderson and Alex Guarnaschelli.

episodes.name: It's All Business
episodes.overview: Chefs and business partners Scott Calhoun and David Feola must challenge each other before they take Bobby Flay down. Meanwhile, Anne Burrell and Michael Symon give Bobby the business.

episodes.name: Smoove Moves
episodes.overview: Comedian JB Smoove teams up with Michael Symon to give Bobby Flay the funny business. Chefs Mia Castro and Brandon Carter aren't here for laughs -- it's serious business in the kitchen as they try to take Bobby down.

episodes.name: Say Yes to the Dish
episodes.overview: Chef Alex Guarnaschelli and fashion designer Randy Fenoli are saying "yes" to chefs Ana Hernandez and Frank Bonanno's dishes -- and "no" to Bobby Flay!

episodes.name: A Deal to Beat Bobby
episodes.overview: Powerhouse entrepreneur Mark Cuban teams up with powerhouse personality Sunny Anderson in the business of beating Bobby Flay. They bring in vegan chefs Tamearra Dyson and Adyre Mason to seal the deal.

episodes.name: Double the Trouble
episodes.overview: Brothers Bryan and Michael Voltaggio tag team in an attempt to throw Bobby Flay off his game. Chefs DeeDee Niyomkul and Juan Carlos Bazan cook up a storm and try to leave Bobby in their dust.

episodes.name: Who's Wayne Is It Anyways?
episodes.overview: Damaris Phillips enlists legendary performer Wayne Brady to team up and distract Bobby Flay with song, dance and a little "foodmance." Chefs Steven Brooks and Becky Brown want to take advantage and get the win.

episodes.name: Chocolate Showdown
episodes.overview: Duff Goldman and Alex Guarnaschelli challenge Bobby Flay to a chocolate battle, but the script gets flipped when chefs Amber Croom and Emily Oyer surprise everyone with a savory chocolate showdown.

episodes.name: Cliff and the Jet
episodes.overview: Chefs Cliff Crooks and Jet Tila join forces to hassle Bobby Flay into a loss. Chefs Kimberly Gamble and Tom Berry get in on the fun and try to topple the king.

episodes.name: Girl Meets Flay
episodes.overview: Molly Yeh leaves the farm to join Alex Guarnaschelli in the Beat Bobby Flay arena. They pin their hopes on chefs Sam Fore and Jon Keeley to bring their game faces and dole out a loss to Bobby.

episodes.name: Let the Good Food Roll
episodes.overview: Anne Burrell and Andy Richter recruit New Orleans chefs Amy Mehrtens and Nathanial Zimet to let the good food roll into Bobby Flay's kitchen in hopes of a win.

episodes.name: Don't Be Nice
episodes.overview: DJ D-Nice and Michael Symon aren't playing nice when they bring out chefs Sue Torres and James Briscione from behind the judges table to try to get a win of their own.

episodes.name: Fowl Shot
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay tries not to get dunked on by basketball legend Amar'e Stoudemire and Katie Lee Biegel. Chefs Michael O'Halloran and Alex Stickland go for the upset win.

episodes.name: Foodie Downer
episodes.overview: Eddie Jackson and actress and comedian Rachel Dratch are hoping to prevent a foodie downer by bringing in chefs Dorian Hunter and Britt Rescigno for a win against Bobby Flay. Womp womp.

episodes.name: Morena and the Marcona
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay tries to make chefs Raymond Yaptinchay and Cara Stadler go nuts in the kitchen. Michael Voltaggio and actress Morena Baccarin are there to cheer them on to victory.

episodes.name: Bobby, Why Don't You Just Meet Me at the Griddle?
episodes.overview: Country music superstar Maren Morris teams up with Sunny Anderson to sing Bobby Flay's swan song. Chefs Matthew Dolan and Thomas Kelly give everyone something to taco 'bout.

episodes.name: Fancy Pants
episodes.overview: In an alliance of fancy folks, Bethenny Frankel and Geoffrey Zakarian team up to out-fancy Bobby Flay. Chefs Chad Rosenthal and Brian Hill are there to frighten him with their food.

episodes.name: Breakfast with Boswell
episodes.overview: Stephanie Boswell and Sunny Anderson bring brunch vibes into the kitchen with chefs Gabriella Baldwin and Jenifer Minelli, who are ready for a win against Bobby Flay!

episodes.name: Get in the Game
episodes.overview: Jaymee Sire and Jeff Mauro bring the energy to wear Bobby Flay down. Chefs Laura Gonzalez and Steven Lingenfelter try to take advantage while Jeff and Jaymee distract Bobby.

episodes.name: You Braise Me Up
episodes.overview: Alex Guarnaschelli and legendary singer Josh Groban hit the high notes and raise up their chefs, Thomas Youell and Diego Sanchez, to grill Bobby Flay in his own kitchen.

episodes.name: BBQ'd Revenge
episodes.overview: BBQ Brawlers Megan Day and David Sandusky are back to seek vengeance against Bobby Flay, who did not pick them for his team on Brawl. BBQ Brawl judges Brooke Williamson and Carson Kressley are there to help them get sweet revenge.

episodes.name: It's Tila Time
episodes.overview: Food Network's favorite couple Jet and Ali Tila bring their Team Tila energy into the kitchen to serve Bobby Flay a loss. Things get heated when chefs Renata Ferraro and Ricky Dolinsky duel it out for a shot against Flay.

episodes.name: High Steaks
episodes.overview: Chefs Trisha Perez Kennealy and Cesar Aldrete face each other in a battle of strip steaks. Their goal is to take down Bobby Flay with the help of Anne Burrell and Josh Capon.

episodes.name: Don't Oaxacaway from Me
episodes.overview: Chefs Noah Zamler and Aerin Zavory are here to make sure Bobby Flay doesn't "Oaxacaway" with the competition. They've got Geoffrey Zakarian and Brooke Williamson on their team to pummel Bobby with pranks.

episodes.name: British Invasion
episodes.overview: British bloke Brooklyn Beckham recruits Sunny Anderson to bring a transatlantic takeover to Bobby Flay's kitchen. Chefs Francis Legge and Caroline Budge are ready to bring the heat from across the pond.

episodes.name: In Bobby's Kitchen, with Amy Sedaris
episodes.overview: Calamity ensues when Amy Sedaris teams up with Michael Symon to take Bobby Flay down. Comfort food queens Kristin Beringson and Amanda Salas are ready to dish out a loss.

episodes.name: A is for Aasif, Alex ... and Ambush!
episodes.overview: Actor and comedian Aasif Mandvi and Chef Alex Guarnaschelli join forces with chefs Diane Lam and Surbi Sahni to test Bobby Flay's abilities and teach him one more A-word: the agony of defeat

episodes.name: You're So Buteau-ful
episodes.overview: Michael Voltaggio and comedian Michelle Buteau keep Bobby Flay in stitches as he tries to work, while chefs Zev Bennett and Petrina Peart stop at nothing to secure a win.

episodes.name: Smoove Operator
episodes.overview: Damaris Phillips and actor JB Smoove are ready to get in Bobby Flay's face if that's what it takes to get a victory. They get help from chefs Christian Gill and Cecelia Valencia, who want to sandwich Bobby out of the kitchen.

episodes.name: Watch the Throne
episodes.overview: Chef Tiffani Faison and The Kitchen's Jeff Mauro give Bobby Flay a royal pain as chefs Roosevelt Ceasar and Natalia Rosario make a run for his crown.

episodes.name: Food, But Make It Fashion
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay takes to the catwalk to try to avoid a loss from Sunny Anderson and Carson Kressley. Chefs Eli Dunn and Kim Mills bring the food and the flair.

episodes.name: Hale to the Chefs
episodes.overview: Comedic actor Tony Hale seeks Amanda Freitag's help to fulfill his childhood dream of conquering Bobby Flay. They've brought in chefs Cristian Rebolledo and Matt Migliore to create a globally inspired dish fit for victory.

episodes.name: Alex, Eric & America vs Bobby
episodes.overview: Chef Alex Guarnaschelli reunites with her Alex vs America host Chef Eric Adjepong to lead the charge for chefs Tomas Chavarria and Tara Monsod to take Bobby Flay down a peg.

episodes.name: Smack Talk City
episodes.overview: Things get feisty in the kitchen when chefs Jarod Farina and Andrew McQuesten start talking smack. Food Network's Eddie Jackson and Buddy Valastro keep up the razzing to throw Bobby Flay off his game.

episodes.name: Just "Dill" With It
episodes.overview: The Kitchen's Alex Guarnaschelli and Jeff Mauro aim to take down Bobby Flay, and chefs Kathy Fang and Natascha Hess get into a pickle with the star ingredient.

episodes.name: New Phone, Who Dis?
episodes.overview: Katie Lee Biegel and David Burtka dial up the distractions while chefs Lambert Givens and Jesse Houston try to ring Bobby Flay's bell.

episodes.name: A Global Gauntlet
episodes.overview: Buddies Anne Burrell and Marc Murphy bring in international cuisine expert chefs Ashten Garrett and Nasser Jaber to challenge Bobby Flay to a global gauntlet.

episodes.name: Bobby's Besties
episodes.overview: Chefs Alex Guarnaschelli and Tanya Holland swap stories about their longtime friend Bobby Flay. Meanwhile, chefs Quincy Randolph and Cam Waron duke it out in the kitchen to try to get a win.

episodes.name: Talk the Shiitake
episodes.overview: Chefs Saif Rahman and Carolina Gomez must walk the walk-y and talk the shiitake to go up against Bobby Flay while Esther Choi and Michael Symon cheer them on.

episodes.name: Kitchen Update
episodes.overview: Saturday Night Live's Colin Jost teams up with Carla Hall and enlists the help of chefs Jo Proul and Katsui Tanabe to make Bobby Flay the butt of the joke.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Casserole with the Punches
episodes.overview: Scott Conant welcomes three of Bobby Flay's besties to attempt a Turkey Day classic -- the casserole; chefs Anne Burrell, Tiffani Faison and Jet Tila bring their best dishes to the table.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Stuff It, Bobby!
episodes.overview: Eddie Jackson brings Thanksgiving game day vibes to Bobby Flay's kitchen, and chefs Maneet Chauhan, Christian Petroni and Michael Psilakis tackle dishes that are stuffed.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Hardest Holiday Dishes
episodes.overview: Giada De Laurentiis decks the halls as triple-threat titans Tiffany Derry, Michael Voltaggio and Brooke Williamson try to put Bobby Flay under the tree with some of the most difficult holiday delicacies.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Room for Dessert
episodes.overview: Carla Hall ushers in an all-pastry holiday extravaganza with chefs Alex Guarnaschelli, Damaris Phillips and Zac Young.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Holiday Throwbacks
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay's favorite holiday elf, Carson Kressley, brings the mischief while chefs Einat Admony, Amanda Freitag and Michael Symon bring some modern flair to classic holiday dishes.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Holiday Around the World
episodes.overview: Geoffrey Zakarian is Bobby Flay's tour guide as chefs Eric Adjepong, Esther Choi and Leah Cohen bring a world of hurt for the holidays.

episodes.name: Bobby, We Need to Talk
episodes.overview: Natalie Morales, host of The Talk, is back in the kitchen with Eddie Jackson. They send chefs Tim Kuklinkski and Sedesh Wilkerson on a mission to beat Bobby Flay in a battle of Scotch eggs.

episodes.name: Don't Be Sour!
episodes.overview: Chopped host Ted Allen and The View's Sara Haines sour Bobby Flay's night while chefs Grace Goudie and Andy Xu try to make lemonade out of their star ingredient.

episodes.name: Drop It Like It's Hot
episodes.overview: Chefs Maneet Chauhan and Brooke Williamson swing by Bobby Flay's kitchen with a "drop challenge" to erase him off the board, while chefs Jocelyn Law-Yone and Rasheeda Purdie school Bobby on their signature dishes.

episodes.name: Kitchen Crime Scene
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay's got a signature dish that's way out of his comfort zone -- and Law & Order's Angie Harmon and Scott Conant aren't making it any easier as they aid and abet chefs Crystal Wahpepah and Adrien Blech.

episodes.name: Under the Tuscan Sun
episodes.overview: Kalen Allen and Anne Burrell help chefs Paolo Calamai and Angelo Competiello show "Roberto" Flay how Tuscan cuisine is done in the old country.

episodes.name: The Room Where It Happens
episodes.overview: Hamilton star Christopher Jackson and Chef Josh Capon double-team Bobby Flay while chefs Edwin Bayone and Kyle McClelland deep-fry his ego.

episodes.name: In Perfect "Hominy"
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay is up to his ears in distractions courtesy of hosts Jaymee Sire and Andrew Zimmern, while chefs Byron Gomez and Sebastien Salomon tussle over a corny star ingredient.

episodes.name: Happy Feet
episodes.overview: Scott Conant and Damaris Phillips pull out all the stops -- including a full-on dance number -- to help contenders Hari Pulapaka and Denis Radovic finish big against Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: This Is How We (Kati) Roll
episodes.overview: The View's Sunny Hostin and Christian Petroni rock Bobby Flay with a kati roll challenge while chefs Romain Paumier and Avishar Barua roll up to Bobby's kitchen.

episodes.name: "Bouillabaisse-ic" Instinct
episodes.overview: Chefs Dan Jackson and Camila Rinaldi are aided and abetted by Sunny Anderson and Jet Tila as they try to slay Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: "Glaser"-Focused
episodes.overview: Comedian Nikki Glaser has Bobby Flay in her sights -- and nothing is off the menu. She and Chef Michael Voltaggio attempt to bring contenders Troy Gardner and Rachel Klein to a vegan victory over Bobby.

32.name: Season 32
32.overview: Flay competes against a who’s who of chefs. For this six episode event series, the competition is expanded to three rounds as Flay teams up with one of the chefs that was just trying to defeat him. First, two of Flay’s chef friends will compete to see who will face off against a third chef waiting in the wings. The winner of that second round will then go on to battle Flay with each one picking one of the eliminated chefs as their sous chef.

episodes.name: A-Team Assemble!
episodes.overview: Two of Bobby Flay's best pals become his worst nightmare. The dynamic duo of Alex Guarnaschelli and Anne Burrell use all their powers to bring chefs Alison Settle and Kevin Scharpf a win.

episodes.name: Make It Work
episodes.overview: Fashion icon Tim Gunn and Carla Hall send chefs Rocco Carulli and Craig Richards down the runway to dress Bobby Flay down.

episodes.name: Who's Your Mac Daddy?
episodes.overview: Eddie Jackson partners with Bobby Flay's kryptonite -- his daughter, Sophie Flay. They bring the family drama center stage while chefs Hari Cameron and Leilani Baugh try to grab a mac 'n' cheese victory.

episodes.name: MMMMBibimbap
episodes.overview: It's all hands on deck as Tiffany Derry and Jet Tila join forces with chefs Chrissy Camba and Johnny Clark to wipe Bobby Flay off the "bibimbap."

episodes.name: Just Another "Flay" in The Office
episodes.overview: Chef Christian Petroni and actress Kate Flannery from The Office recruit chefs Josh Gale and Christian Ortiz for a hostile takeover of Bobby Flay's kitchen.

episodes.name: The "Win" Beneath Their Wings
episodes.overview: It's a BBQ bash, and Bobby Flay's getting burned when Kardea Brown and Carson Kressley boost chefs Rashad Jones and Kent Rollins to soar to a winged win.

episodes.name: The Bald and the Beautiful
episodes.overview: Supermodel and swimwear designer Devon Windsor teams up with Chef Michael Symon to keep the drama high while chefs Dom Crisp and Santiago Guzzetti try to cook up a win against Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Ready for Their Close Up
episodes.overview: Chef Geoffrey Zakarian and model Ashley Graham strike a pose to distract Bobby Flay while chefs Maiya Keck and Brian Cripps go in for the win.

episodes.name: Bottoms Up, Bobby Down!
episodes.overview: Actress, comedian and foodie Aisha Tyler and Katie Lee Biegel get crafty and ply Bobby Flay with cocktails while chefs Jeff Potts and Brittney Williams toast their path to victory.

episodes.name: Turn Down for What?!?
episodes.overview: Hip-hop icon Lil Jon and Anne Burrell get Bobby Flay's kitchen "turnt up" with lights, beats and bottle service. Chefs Eva Pesantez and Robert Butts have Bobby on the VIP list ... to lose.

episodes.name: A "Matcha" Made in Heaven
episodes.overview: Pastry chef Stephanie Boswell and actress Anika Noni Rose see chefs Lindsey Farr and Yara Lamers through a matcha battle as they prepare to make Bobby Flay green with envy at their pastry prowess.

episodes.name: Shock, Awe and Shakshuka
episodes.overview: Chef Michael Voltaggio and actress Ellie Kemper bring the pain as chefs Travis McGinty and Suzanne Vizethann crack more than a few eggs in their quest to take down Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Nashville Hot, Bobby ... Not
episodes.overview: Country music superstar Martina McBride and Chef Alex Guarnaschelli jam with chefs Drew Erickson and Aristide Williams to tune Bobby Flay up.

episodes.name: This Kitchen's Crowded
episodes.overview: Kardea Brown and actor Kevin Pollak try to crowd Bobby Flay out of his own kitchen, making room for chefs Carlos Anthony and Nelson German to score a win.

episodes.name: Cheri Takes the Cake
episodes.overview: Pastry chef Zac Young and SNL alum Cheri Oteri are the perfect pair to ruin Bobby Flay's night. They recruit pastry powerhouses Joe Murphy and Laura Ochikubo to turn up the heat.

episodes.name: Brooke and Crooks Cook Up a Win
episodes.overview: Chefs Brooke Williamson and Cliff Crooks take the fight to the kitchen when they back contenders Javier Canteras and Emiliano Marentes to crack Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Cat Fight
episodes.overview: Oscar-nominated actress Gabourey Sidibe bonds with fellow cat fancier Chef Damaris Phillips while chefs Malik Rhasaan and Sean Pharr attempt to claw their way to victory against Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Fashion-Forward
episodes.overview: Fashion maven Carson Kressley and Chef Amanda Freitag help chefs Maria Mazon and Guillermo Pernot cook up a win against Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Full Frontal Assault
episodes.overview: Comedian Samantha Bee and Michael Symon go all out to derail Bobby Flay so chefs Johnny Alvarez and Stanton Bundy can score a win.

episodes.name: Why So "Sear-ious"?
episodes.overview: BBQ Brawl veterans Carson Kressley and Rodney Scott reunite to put Bobby Flay's feet to the fire and bring home a well-charred win for chefs Kwasi Kwaa and Winnie Yee-Lakhani.

episodes.name: It's Always Sunny in Kashmir
episodes.overview: Sunny Anderson and Scott Conant team up with chefs Maryam Ghaznavi and Deepak Kaul to school Bobby Flay in new worlds of flavor.

episodes.name: What a "Dump-ling"!
episodes.overview: Chefs Anne Burrell and Eddie Jackson bring the noise as chefs Jessica Yarr and Matthew Zafrir bring the flavor to dump Bobby Flay in a pierogi battle.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Turkey Day Traditions
episodes.overview: Katie Lee Biegel cracks the wishbone with Turkey Day classics and makes this holiday reunion a surprise family affair. Chefs Darnell Ferguson, Bryan Voltaggio and Michael Voltaggio attempt to squash Bobby Flay by leveling the playing field with a new turkey tradition.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Holiday Leftover Revival
episodes.overview: It's a Chopped takeover as Tiffani Faison welcomes her fellow judges to second helpings of competition and mystery ingredients they'll transform into Thanksgiving masterpieces. Chefs Marc Murphy, Amanda Freitag and Scott Conant battle Bobby Flay to see if they can knock the stuffing out of him in a leftover showdown that hopefully leaves Bobby eating the humblest pie.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: 12 Ways to Beat Bobby
episodes.overview: The always festive Carson Kressley gifts Bobby Flay with a partridge in a pear tree this holiday season, and chefs Chris Scott, Justin Sutherland and Tiffany Derry devise 12 ways to beat Bobby in an attempt to ruffle his feathers. Carson orchestrates a final festive surprise in round three and brings in some special guests.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Holiday Brunchin'
episodes.overview: Pass the mimosas and holiday nog because Bobby Flay's daughter, Sophie Flay, is in the house. Chefs Zac Young, Eddie Jackson and Maneet Chauhan attempt to smoke Bobby and test his knowledge of international holiday flavors in the ultimate brunch battle.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Feeling Frosted
episodes.overview: Holiday queen Sunny Anderson sprinkles seasonal cheer with sugar, spice and everything nice. Chefs Stephanie Izard, Damaris Phillips and Duff Goldman challenge Bobby Flay to the ultimate baking battle as they whip up some festive, frosted treats in a bid to land a sweet victory and leave Bobby iced out.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Feast of the Seven Fishes
episodes.overview: It's sink or swim as Alex Guarnaschelli recruits Antonia Lofaso, Christian Petroni and Michael Symon for an Italian showdown of gladiator proportions. These culinary titans celebrate all things seafood and pull off an epic feast of the seven fishes that Bobby Flay will never forget.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Time to Celebrate!
episodes.overview: Jeff Mauro is in the house, ready to serenade chefs Brooke Williamson, Jet Tila and Andrew Zimmern. They go all out with fancy ingredients, prime cuts and fierce competition, along with an over-the-top holiday feast designed to celebrate Bobby Flay's demise.

34.name: Season 34
34.overview: The Food Network family is challenging Bobby Flay to face his worst holiday nightmares. In each supersized hour, familiar faces battle it out to choose the final challenge and pick the teams in this epic holiday throwdown!

episodes.name: The (Steak) Oscar Goes to...
episodes.overview: "The Kitchen" co-hosts Sunny Anderson and Geoffrey Zakarian come together to escort chefs Paddy Coker and Greg Lutes down the red carpet and snub Bobby Flay along the way.

episodes.name: Tall, Dark and Handsome
episodes.overview: The dashing Scott Conant and Eric Adjepong unite with chefs Dane Blom and Emme Ribeiro Collins to gang up on Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Mentor vs. Mentee
episodes.overview: Chef Bryan Romero attempts to take down his mentor, Chef Marc Quinones, in a mean bean battle, while Michael Voltaggio and Damaris Phillips cheer them on towards victory over Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Don't Yuck My Yum
episodes.overview: Sunny Anderson and TV host Ross Mathews team up with chefs Kaleena Bliss and Melissa Donahue-Talmage to boil up a win against Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: On a Roll!
episodes.overview: Eddie Jackson and Maneet Chauhan pull out all the stops to help chefs Bernard Bennett and Lena Le roll out a victory over Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: JUDGEment Day
episodes.overview: Brooke Williamson and actor Matt Walsh encourage BBF judges Ariel Fox and Jae Lee to show Bobby Flay how it's done.

episodes.name: Raise the Steaks
episodes.overview: Michael Symon and comedian Chris Redd leave Bobby Flay in tears while chefs Adam Pawlak and Page Pressley impress with their takes on a classic.

episodes.name: Tame the Lion's Mane
episodes.overview: Michael Voltaggio and Christian Petroni choose chefs Lanny Chin and Wendy Zeng to tackle a tricky star ingredient in hopes of defeating Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: A Bitter Pill to Swallow
episodes.overview: Alex Guarnaschelli and Katie Lee Biegel get behind chefs Kyungbin Min and Alex Ottusch, while Bobby Flay cooks up his secret weapon.

episodes.name: Shrimply the Best
episodes.overview: Chefs Tony Smith and Sterling Buckley hold a shrimp scrimmage while Scott Conant and singer Jana Kramer distract Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Sweet Defeat
episodes.overview: Duff Goldman and actress Alyson Hannigan join forces with pastry pros Jewel Johnson and Katherine Sprung to take down Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Ciao Ciao, Bobby!
episodes.overview: Alex Guarnaschelli reunites with her Ciao House co-host, Gabriele Bertaccini, to lead chefs Rachelle Murphy and Jackson Kalb to a world of "pasta-bilities" in beating Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: All-Star Showdown
episodes.overview: All-star chefs Shirley Chung and Tim Hollingsworth leave Bobby Flay in the dust as Carla Hall and The View's Ana Navarro uplift the audience.

episodes.name: Anchors Aweigh
episodes.overview: Eddie Jackson and CNN's Poppy Harlow break the news to Bobby Flay that he's going to lose. Chefs Dayna Lee and Enrique Lozano hope to flatten the competition.

episodes.name: No "Flay" at the Beach
episodes.overview: Surf's up, but Bobby Flay's going down when Jet Tila and Jesse Palmer lead a summertime jam with chefs Demetrius Brown and Pablo Lamon.

episodes.name: Bring on the Brits!
episodes.overview: Chef Michael Symon and Shark Tank's Robert Herjavec recruit chefs Poppy O'Toole and Joel Childs to master English specialties and mash up Bobby Flay in the competition.

episodes.name: Dance, Dance Revolution
episodes.overview: Chef Carla Hall and professional dancer Allison Holker Boss bring the moves as chefs Kimberly Plafke and Tiana Gee try to bring Bobby Flay a sweet defeat.

episodes.name: Say What?!
episodes.overview: Bobby Flay is served a signature dish that's way out of his comfort zone as Chopped host Ted Allen and Chef Tiffani Faison root for chefs Jim Armstrong and Earl James Reynolds to take him down.

episodes.name: Broadway Bound!
episodes.overview: Chef Jet Tila and actor Sutton Foster create a new musical for Bobby Flay, while pastry chefs Kaitlin Guerin and Laura Warren attempt to whip up a win.

episodes.name: News You Can Use
episodes.overview: Chef Geoffrey Zakarian and CNN's Kate Bolduan break the news to chefs Zack Roth and Milena Pagán -- they've got to beat Bobby Flay!

episodes.name: Loud and Proud
episodes.overview: Chef Antonia Lofaso partners with comedian Leslie Jones to bring the nuttiness as chefs Josh Elliot and Vicky Colas attempt to get the last laugh over Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Breakfast of Champions
episodes.overview: Pastry chef Duff Goldman and journalist Gayle King interrogate Bobby Flay, while chefs Brian Ingram and Dayana Joseph cook up a breakfast of champions.

episodes.name: The "Thai" That Binds
episodes.overview: Food Network favorite Sunny Anderson and actor Jenna Elfman team up with chefs Francisco Higareda and Chris Dodson to crush Bobby Flay with their international flavors.

episodes.name: Red Carpet Ready
episodes.overview: Chef Katie Lee Biegel and fashion icon Carson Kressley glam it up while, chefs Rob Reinsmith and Manny Barella dress Bobby Flay down.

episodes.name: This is ... Competition!
episodes.overview: Chef Michael Symon and This Is Us actor Chrissy Metz put their heads together and noodle up a way to help chefs Loic Sany and Taylor Haupt prevail against Bobby Flay.

episodes.name: Game Day Grapple
episodes.overview: Chef Eddie Jackson and NFL Network Insider Ian Rapoport huddle up with chefs Nick Shipp and Natalie Blake as they try to get Bobby Flay to fumble.

episodes.name: Talk the Talk and Walk the Walk
episodes.overview: Chef Jet Tila and The Talk's Amanda Kloots distract Bobby Flay as chefs Nikolaos Kaperneros and Monique Feybesse create fruity masterpieces.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Bird Is Not the Word
episodes.overview: Eddie Jackson kicks off the holiday season with a turkey-less Thanksgiving celebration. Chefs Christian Petroni, Adrienne Cheatham and Michael Voltaggio show Bobby Flay that the side dishes are the stars on this year's dining table.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Pie in the Sky
episodes.overview: The legendary Ina Garten passes the whipped cream as she recruits chefs Amanda Freitag, Aarti Sequeira and Duff Goldman to serve Bobby Flay a slice of humble pie. In each round, these star chefs bake up an ode to everyone's favorite Thanksgiving dessert.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Magic of the Holidays
episodes.overview: The ever festive Carson Kressley makes a grand entrance as he sets out to remind Bobby Flay why the holidays are so iconic. Chefs Tiffani Faison, Tiffany Derry and Scott Conant are in for a big surprise in the final round when they're treated to a magical performance.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Global Holiday Markets
episodes.overview: Sunny Anderson takes Bobby Flay on a trip around the world with chefs Gabe Bertaccini, Marcus Samuelsson and Maneet Chauhan. Each round, the acclaimed chefs celebrate ingredients that are commonly found at holiday markets across the globe.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Roasted and Toasted
episodes.overview: Michael Symon gathers his friends, chefs Jet Tila, Antonia Lofaso and Geoffrey Zakarian, together to get Bobby Flay roasted and toasted! The drinks are flowing and the insults are glowing as Bobby attempts to leave this holiday party unscathed.

episodes.name: Holiday Throwdown: Happy New Year!
episodes.overview: Jeff Mauro brings the pomp and circumstance to round out the holiday season with an epic New Year's bash. Chefs Damaris Phillips, Eric Adjepong and Brooke Williamson make a resolution to beat Bobby Flay!
